%N A394810 Decimal expansion of 3*Pi - 12/Pi.
%C A394810 The mean perimeter of a spherical triangle defined by 3 great circles independently and uniformly selected at random on the unit sphere (Santaló, 2004).
%C A394810 The triangle is formed by the intersection of 3 hemispheres whose poles are 3 points independently and uniformly selected at random on the sphere.
%D A394810 Luis A. Santaló, Integral Geometry and Geometric Probability, 2nd ed., Cambridge University Press, 2004, p. 313, note 8.
